#5400
The Altar to the Gods.~
You stand before the altar to the gods. The top of the altar is made of
a transparent glass. Inside the glass you see what appears to be a dark
storm. Black rainclouds and shadows dance within the glass in an endless
dance. The altars legs are made of pure gold. This altar must have been
built by the gods themselves. The room that holds the altar is also a 
marvel to behold. Unlike the rest of this room as you look upwards you
do not see a roof. Instead, you behold a glorious sight; a mass of light
and darkness swirling in many directions. It is as if the gods themselves
are part of this room. It might be that that swirling mass is a portal
to the heavens. The rest of this room is decorated in many ancient 
tapestries depicting wars and legends. The northern tapestry is a bit 
strange though. A towering drow mage holding his hands up high grins at
you as if he is almost lifelike. The tapestry seems to be moving very
slightly, as if something about it is out of place.
~
