#5401
The steps to the altar.~
As you stand on the steps before the altar, you see two thirty feet tall
statues on either side of you. The statue to the west is an elven ranger.
as you look upon him you notice the entricate workmanship. The face seems
to be almost lifelike. The elf is posed in a battle stance. His bow
is in hand and he is pulling back on the string with an arrow readied to
let loose. He wears a long cloak that is pulled up over his body. The
statue to the east is much more different. This statue is of a human woman.
Then you notice that she isn't a human, but a vampire! The statue has her
arms folded and she is wearing a grin on her delicate face. You wonder
what importance these statues have here. They stand freely on both sides 
towering over the rest of this temple. The stairs that you stand on are made
from fine polished black marble. The room is very quiet.
~
